> >So I've got some kernel patches to disable beeps and blips from the internal 
> >speaker.
> 
> What is wrong with "setterm -blength 0" and "xset -b off"?
Doesn't always work. For example, at work we require the console to be
VT100, beeps with that terminal cannot be killed using setterm -blength
0. Don't ask me why they want it at VT100, I was overruled. 
